This is what tourist guides will tell you.
The building sits astride at the end of the platform with a tower on every corner of the front, indistinguishable from some provincial German town hall.
The stone is dirty.
The whole building is slowly falling apart.
But once one gets inside the vaulted cash register, one can no longer have a doubt about the size of the business whose westernmost gate of the station was.
The station was opened in August 1908 by the German consortium of the Anatolian-Baghdad Corporation.
