The proposal came at a time when Eatonville was still coming out of a difficult historical period.
Forced integration, along with other things, has ended the relatively idyllic isolation of this community.
In the 1950s, the struggle to mix races brought hatred to the threshold of the community.
"At the time, a bunch of white boys, they came and threw oranges and things on people sitting on the side," Franklin said.
