In a 1955 letter to The Orlando Sentinel, Hurston questioned the Supreme Court's demand for forced integration, and her decision in the Brown case against the Chamber of Education said it was "insulting to my race rather than glorifying."
Residents now claim that the desegregation of schools, even though it was positive in some areas, reduced cohesion in Eatonville and undermined the courage of the local youth.
