It is worth mentioning, for example, the innovative design, the new platform, larger dimensions and new engines.
Even before we explore the new model, it should be noted that the new Jazz comes to market six years after the launch of the first generation.
Therefore, the first thing we will notice is the fact that Honda needed a shorter period to rejuvenate this model than other manufacturers.
Although Jazz is a lesser-known model in Europe, it has become a phenomenon in other markets.
This is the case for Japan, the country where Jazz was the best-selling car in 2002, and also during this year 2008.
It has sold almost a million copies in Japan since the launch of Honda Jazz.
The second market became the old continent with approximately half a million units sold in six years.
Honda, however, aims to increase sales in its category for the new Jazz.
Thus, while in 2007 the Japanese company sold a total of 83 000 Honda Jazz, in 2009 estimates counted with 100 000 cars, which would increase by 17% in the European market.
As for the Spanish market, Honda has sold a total of 8,000 Jazz units since 2002, which translates to 6.7% of Honda's total sales in Spain.
In terms of the new generation of Jazz, the management of the Spanish branch expects to sell 2 000 units for the whole year.
It is the arrival of the new Jazz that will allow Honda to significantly mitigate the decline in sales in Spain.
The automaker’s management is de facto expecting the end of the year with a total of 22,000 units sold, which means 4,000 fewer than in 2007 and a decrease of 16%.
Despite this increase in sales, Honda increased its share of the Spanish market to 1.8%, compared to 1.6% last year.
In 2010, the Japanese company expects to reach 2%.
To achieve this share, Honda relies on the success of its next new model.
It is a Honda Insight, a five-door hybrid of compact size with a length of 4.37 meters, from which the Japanese company promises worldwide sales of approximately 200 000 units a year.
In terms of markets, according to Japanese manufacturer's estimates, 50% of Insight is sold in the United States, while the remaining percentages will be split by the old continent and Japan.
The start of Honda Insight's sales is expected in the first months of next year once it is unveiled to the public in Valencia in January.
Compared to the first generation, the new Jazz has increased all dimensions.
Its length increased to 3.9 meters (five centimeters more), the width to 1.69 meters (two centimeters more) and the wheelbase to 2.5 meters, which means an extension of five centimeters.
The height, on the other hand, has not changed and is still 1.52 meters.
The increase in dimensions also increased the interior.
This advantage was achieved both by using a new platform and by storing the fuel tank in the middle of the car, which was already used in the previous Honda Jazz.
Also, the volume of the luggage compartment - which has a double bottom system - increased to 399 liters, 19 liters more than the volume of the luggage compartment in the first generation.
It should be noted that these dimensions occur with the 1.4 engine version, since the luggage compartment volume of the Honda Jazz 1.2 is 379 liters.
Another improvement, in addition to the exterior elements - such as the rear LED lights or the possibility of equipping with a glass panoramic roof - is easier access to the rear seats.
The door leading to the second row of seats allows the opening angle of 80 degrees compared to 67 in the first Jazz model.
With the second-generation Honda Jazz, the engines are also new.
Initially, this small model will be offered with two gasoline engines of 1.2 and 1.4 liters.
Both engines use i-VTEC technology, which allows for lower consumption, lower carbon dioxide emissions and delivers excellent improvements to the propulsion system at the same time with high torque in full engine speed.
The first 1.2-litre engine has a power of 90 hp at 6,000 rpm with a maximum torque of 114 Nm at 4,900 rpm.
This engine - which had 78 horsepower in the previous generation of the Jazz - consumes 5.3 liters and emissions of 125 grams of CO2.
Compared to the previous engine, which in the previous generation was 83 hp, the current one will reach 100.
The Honda Jazz 1.4 with 100 hp has a combined consumption of 5.4 liters and an emission of 128 grams of CO2.
