The restriction essentially means that if the Ministry buys as part of the auction, a tax premium will be imposed on the golden parachutes if the fallen bank directors are not sent straight to retirement.
In the event of a direct purchase of low-quality loans, the government will aggressively intervene in the interest of ensuring that the money for management is not exaggerated.
It should be added that the existing contracts for gold parachutes will not change, the restriction only applies to new contracts, which is intended to be another stimulus to participate in the programme.
"This is the first case in U.S. history where the statutory restrictions on CEOs' remuneration will be in effect," House of Representatives' House of Representatives Committee Chairman Barney Frank said in a statement.
In addition, the state in the banks participating in the program will have the right to acquire a share, thereby reducing the risk of taxpayers, because once the economy and the rescued bank get on their feet, they can even profit from this transaction.
