Prices in the electricity, gas and water sector outperformed prices from the previous year by 18.7 percent.
In terms of division by sector focus, the highest monthly price increase (0.7 percent) in the tangible asset production sectors was reflected in domestic sales in August.
In the consumer goods sectors, prices rose by 0.3 percent, in the energy of processing and further processing sectors, prices were unchanged due to the previous month.
The biggest price increases, given the same month of the previous year, could be observed in the energy of the processing and processing sectors (16.8 percent) in August 2008.
In the consumer goods industries, we measured a price increase of 6.8 percent, while in the case of tangible assets, we measured a price decrease of 1.4 percent.
